<promed@promedmail.org>
[Thank you, all. The variation in numbers hospitalized must await
clarification. Drought is not just an absence of rain but also indicative
of high heat-stress, which can affect the immunogenesis of livestock.
Grazing livestock are forced to graze lower lying areas were anthrax spores
may have collected and in grazing acquire soil & spores. Subsequent cases
would come from eating contaminated bloody (salty) soil around dead
animals. Pigs are normally fairly resistant and this animal may well have
become infected by feeding on a carcass or as a result of eating the
intestines of a butchered sick animal.
The best control process is to vaccinate stock promptly and to ensure that
all carcasses, and contaminated soil, is burnt. Burying can result in
long-term contaminated grave sites.
On another but parallel subject it is being claimed that the current series
of anthrax reports are part of some hoax activity in support of a PR
campaign for human vaccination and AVIP. I would point out that ProMED-mail
has been reporting human and animal anthrax from the beginning 5-6 years
ago; secondly, we are in the northern hemisphere "anthrax season -- July to
September -- and therefore outbreak reports are not unusual; thirdly,
thanks in part to ProMED-mail, disease reporting has increased worldwide so
we have more news reports to utilise; fourthly, livestock anthrax is rarely
reported by such sources unless there are human cases - which
epidemiologically puts the cart before the horse -- the working ratios are
ten to twenty cattle deaths for each human cutaneous case, 200 human
cutaneous cases per reported gastroenteric case, and in Africa about 64
infected animals are butchered, cooked and eaten for each outbreak of
gastroenteric anthrax with the better the cook, the greater the risk of
disease. And lastly that the Chinese, Japanese, and Russian news agencies
should be in some cabal with AVIP boggles the mind. This particular thread
is cut. Discussion on it will not be entertained. - MHJ
...................jw/mhj/es
